name: Paxata Tech Talk: ES2015 and the next generation of JS languages
desc: Now that the new spec for Javascript has been released it is time to catch up! During this presentation we will look at the changes to both the code and the ecosystem brought on by ES2015. We will explore how it will change frameworks like D3, Angular and React. Finally, we will explore how Paxata is working to upgrade from a legacy Angular 1 world to the promise of and Angular 2 one powered by Typescript.

name: Lean-In: Empowering Women in Technology
desc: Join ACM-W's next Lean In discussion on empowering women to achieve their dreams despite the challenges and gender biases in our workplace, classroom, and personal settings. Our members will also be chatting about our experiences at the Grace Hopper Celebration conference.

name: Tech Women Change the World - A Talk by Lauren Kinsey
desc: Lauren Kinsey is an expert on the intersection of gender and technology. A TEDx speaker and invited guest speaker at MIT, she has a talent for making her audiences feel engaged and motivated. She is the creator of womenintechsuccess.com and genderbalancechampion.com. Most recently, she designed a seven-step algorithm for gender balance, called SCALE UP.  Lauren claims tech companies using SCALE UP are guaranteed to achieve gender balance within five years of full implementation. Lauren has two main side projects she’s currently focused on. The first is working on a book about what cities can do to earn a reputation as a, “Top City for Women in Tech.” The second is blogging about information security at “Making Sense of Security.”

name: Fall Picnic + Team Formation Social
desc: Join us for ACM-W’s annual fall picnic! Meet awesome people, enjoy some free Canes, and find your teammates for the upcoming hackathon, HackOHI/O. Raising Canes will be sponsored by Brooksource; feel free to bring resumes if you’re looking for internship or job opportunities.

name: CEO Networking and Q&A Panel - Hosted with Harvard Undergraduate Women in Business
desc: Students from all majors are invited to come and learn more about how to incorporate business into their course of study, as well as how entrepreneurs in the area have gotten their start. You’ll get insight from our featured speakers on what types of companies are in the area, how they developed their own companies, and what tools and advice they picked up along the way.  As well as meeting up with other students from various majors all with an interest in business!

name: ACM-W Social + Resume Review
desc: Come hang out and get to know some of the other women in computer science! ACM-W members that have interned at major tech companies will also be there to review your resume help you figure out how to make it stand out to recruiters.

name: Collaborative analytics: Meeting global challenges through shared research and development
desc: This talk will focus on research collaborations that cut across disciplinary, organizational, and geographical boundaries to generate research and development breakthroughs on global challenges such as healthcare and climate change. Pushing the state of the art can be facilitated through these partnerships--public/private and academic/industry--when each group bring their unique strengths and perspectives to bear on scientific problems.

name: HMB Tech Talk
desc:
Moving From College to Enterprise: What to Expect when Entering the Industry
After graduation, students quickly discover the real world can be very different from the classroom.
